  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Note: subsequent to the original validation campaign (completed Q2 2023), the clinical use envelope was expanded to include a paediatric sub-population (body surface area 0.5–1.0 m², flow range 0.8–2.0 L/min) following a post-market protocol amendment dated Q4 2023. The credibility team has determined that the existing validation dataset, which covers adult flow rates of 3.0–6.0 L/min at impeller speeds 2000–3500 RPM, provides sufficient coverage for the expanded envelope on the basis that the underlying turbulence and shear-stress scaling relationships are regime-independent. No new experimental validation points for the paediatric flow range have been collected, and no re-calibration evidence is linked to this package.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
